Apr 5 2009 	Better than expected	After reading the latest reviews of this hotel (before we left) me and my mum were a bit uncertain about whether we should find a new hotel or not. Now I'm glad we decided to give this hotel a try! It wasn't at all as bad as many people made it sound! We asked for a room on a lower floor because of my mum's back problems, even though we've read that the Underground was &quot;unbarable&quot; lower down. We got a twin room on the first floor. We didn't mind about the Underground, sure, it made some noise but on the evenings the trains didn't go very often. The room was quite small but ok, I mean, you don't go to London to sit at the hotel all the time. We had a window with a view of a brick wall, again, we didn't mind. At least there was a window! The bathroom was clean and modern and we also had a bathtub. The thing is - we couldn't use the tub because we could only get water from the shower thing and while filling the tub from the shower the water almost got cold. There was a rather large color tv in the room, hairdryer, telephone and coffee- and tea making facilities.The room was overall a bit worn out but the beds were comfortable. It was very hot in the room, we tried to turn down the heat but it didn't work so we kept the window open which was a bit of a challenge but the room got cooler. There was also free wireless internet access that I could use in the room and not only in the common areas.All of the staff was nice and friendly. One thing was a bit odd - when you left the room you had to leave the key at the reception and then get in when you came back. They said it was for safety reasons. The hotel had a luggage room where you could leave your luggage before checking in and after checking out which was very good so you didn't have to carry it all around! Breakfast was totally ok, toast with different sorts of jam, cereal, milk, juice, tea and coffee. There could've been some cheese too, but other from that it was good. Location of this hotel is excellent - just a couple of minutes walk from Notting Hill Gate, shops, food, parks and of course Portobello Road. And it is beautifully located just near Pembridge Square.	
