Apr 2 2009 	Great value for the money	After reading some of the reviews for this hotel, we almost cancelled our reservation. But then we realized that most of the reviews on the other hotels we were looking at were also negative so it seems that people are quick to complain, but do not always take the time to compliment. So here is a different opinion of Blue Bells: We stayed for 6 nights, and we had a room on the top floor. There is no elevator, so getting the bags upstairs was a bit of a struggle, but lack of an elevator is common in European hotels in this category, so that was not an unexpected problem. The room was large with 2 twin beds and a television. Both the room and the modern bathroom were very clean and the towels provided were as large as beach towels, much better than you find at budget hotels in the US. There is a hairdryer in the bathroom, so no need to bring one from home. There was also a refrigerator in the room, and the staff was more than accommodating in providing glasses for us take to our room so we could enjoy cold drinks. There was an electric pot for heating water, which was helpful when my companion caught a cold and needed to take medicine dissolved in hot water. All in all, the room was very comfortable and perfect for our needs. You do hear the Underground from time to time (even on the top floor) but it does not run all night, so it did not bother us. I can imagine if you were on a lower floor you might have more of a problem with that. Surprisingly, the walls are not soundproof, so we could hear quite a bit of noise from our neighbors. But that is not the fault of the hotel, that is the fault with people not being considerate of others around them and being too loud late at night. But again, it was not that much of a problem. About the only complaint that I would have about the room was that there was not good lighting by the beds. The only light in the room was the main overhead light. It would have been nice to have a light by the bedside. The breakfast was simple but satisfying (toast, cereal, orange juice, tea/coffee). If you are looking for more than that, you would have to go out. But it was typical of a continental breakfast in many hotels and the service was always prompt and friendly. The staff at the hotel was helpful and accommodating. There is a computer for guests to use in the breakfast room, so we were able to check online for tours and activities. That was a big surprise as most hotels in this category don't have internet access for their guests. All in all, we thoroughly enjoyed our stay and would not hesitate to go back. We definitely got our money's worth. At the rate we paid, we were not expecting a deluxe hotel, and it is certainly not in that category, but for a moderate hotel, it was great. The staff did admit that some of their rooms are not as nice as others, so you would want to be sure to request a room on the upper floors. It was worth climbing the stairs to get to a better room. Oh, and they do have a room for storing luggage if you arrive early or leave late. That was a big plus when we arrived as we could just drop off our suitcases and get started seeing the sights!	
