Aug 19 2007 	better than expected	My boyfriend and I spent 2 nights in summer 2007, 1 night in the twin bedroom and 1 night in the double bedroom. Before checking into this hotel, we had read a range of reviews. Hence, we had insisted on a room above ground level to avoid rumbling from the train line. True to expectations, the twin bedroom was claustrophobic, nondescript, with the bare essentials but clean. The double bedroom was airy, included a minifridge which was handy, and a very pleasantly clean bathroom. The rumbling can be largely ignored. At such a price, its location and pleasant surroundings, and for anyone who plans to spend little time in the room, this hotel is definitely worth recommending.	
