Dec 11 2006 	Very dodgy but great location	If – and it’s a big if -- you can ignore the rumble from the underground, the dodgy security, the stiflingly overheated rooms and the seriously half-arsed housekeeping, this is a handy place to stay – close to three tube stations, good pubs, restaurants and shopping. Heating: Though our first floor room window was right above the rooftop of another building (and without a lock) we were forced to sleep with the window wide open in December because the heating was set so high.Security: When I asked to see a room, the guy on reception gave me the master key to every room, stayed at his desk, and left me to it. Luckily for other guests I’m honest, but this astonishingly lax attitude worried us for the remainder of our stay.Housekeeping: In a word, woeful. Maid (the owner’ wife?) arrived to clean our room at an inconvenient time -- there was no ‘no not disturb’ option -- and we asked her to come back in ten minutes. She didn’t come back at all. Next day, bed was roughly pulled up, not made, bathroom was not cleaned and cups and glasses were left dirty.All day, every day, dirty linen was piled up on the first floor landing.The underground: Yes, the room rumbles every couple of minutes, but we got used to it. Conclusion: This is a reasonably priced hotel in an insanely expensive city. It’s got a LOT of problems, but if you don’t spent a lot of time in your room, there are worse places to put your head down.	
