Jun 27 2006	Great Hotel Excellent Location	My family of 4 (including two college students) stayed at the Blue Bells Hotel in late June, 2006 for 8 days in a quad room. This was our first trip abroad so we came with no expectations and we were very pleased with the hotel. You can't beat the location or the quiet street. Round the corner from the Tube and bus stops on Bayswater Road, many restaurants and restaurant chains nearby. Also, 2 movie theatres down the street. One morning we slept in until 9 a.m. because it was so quiet outside even with the window open. We couldn't hear anyone else in the hotel unless we went downstairs to breakfast. The rumble of the Tube was not a problem for us. Our room was upstairs about 3 levels in the front of the hotel.The room was equipped with a fan which helped circulate air and the bathroom was fine, small but adequate. Large towels which are a big deal for us. Water pressure good in the bathtub/shower combo. The beds were comfortable (no bed bugs!), the staff friendly and always helpful with an additional towel. They also booked our taxi back to Heathrow and it was on time and at a booked rate. Two nice things about the hotel: It has a computer for guest use in the family dining area which was accessible day/night. Also, the continental breakfast was very nice. Tea, coffee, toast, cereals, juice, fruit, etc. Since the price of food is so high in London having g an early breakfast was good.The hotel has a homey feel, seems to cater to families. We would definitely stay there again.	
