Jul 31 2004	We took a chance and found a winner!	I didn't know anything about this hotel, and booked it based on a phone conversation with one of the hotel managers and looking at their website(--------------------------). It is a building built in the 1890's(?) that has been completely rennovated(two years ago?), and was formerly called The Blue Bells Hotel. It has a bathroom w/ shower/bathtub in each room(a little difficult to find in London). We stayed in the large family room on the ground floor(pictured on their website), and were extremely pleased, especially after hearing about smaller more expensive rooms in London. The breakfast is basic(cereal, toast, fruit, coffee, juice), but was included in our room price, and we ate there 6/7 mornings. They also have an electric teapot in the room for making tea and coffee. The staff is also very friendly, and always quick to help us with whatever we needed, including our many requests for extra towels and finding us a cheaper way to get to the airport than the black taxi's.  The area this hotel is in(Pembridge Square) is absolutely gorgeous. There is a center square(garden) surrounded by buildings all similar to the hotel. The hotel is only approximately a 5 minute walk from the Nottinghill Gate underground stop, which made it very convenient to get to many places. One of the buildings two buildings down the street is a small boys school, which we found out is where Princess Diana's boys went to when they were younger. There were only two minor downsides to this hotel, both of which would not keep me from having it as my first choice next time in London. The first is that we were promised early checkin, but when we arrived at approximately 10am, our room was not available due to the fact that it was occupied the previous night. But, they had their staff drop what they were doing and quickly concentrate on our room and we had it within an hour - impressive. The second minor downside was that the Central line (subway/underground) runs somewhere underneath the hotel. There is a very minor rumbling, but not enough to keep our kids from going to sleep or wake them up(one is a light sleeper). If we weren't staying on the ground floor, we probably wouldn't even hear it. As I said, both very minor shortcomings. One additional note - we had problems sending email from San Antonio to their email address, so if they seem to be ignoring your email, they're not - just give them a call. Again, this place was top notch - great location, nice clean rooms, great price, and a friendly and attentive staff. It will be my first choice next time I am in London.	
